  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n2. Customer identification and verification procedures\n3. Monitoring and reporting suspicious transactions\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Implementing compliance programs\n6. Imposing penalties for non-compliance\n\nExamples include:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) in the United States\n- Money Laundering Regulations in the United Kingdom\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) international standards\n\nThese regulations apply to banks, credit unions, investment firms, and other financial service providers.",
